WEBVTT

00:13.888 --> 00:15.807
[dramatic instrumental music plays]

00:23.064 --> 00:25.358
[Pogo] On April the 1st, 2019,

00:25.442 --> 00:28.570
the Earth was destroyed
in a cataclysmic event.

00:30.655 --> 00:33.575
Billions of people were wiped out
in a matter of minutes.

00:34.576 --> 00:37.579
Ironically, the six survivors
of the apocalypse

00:37.662 --> 00:39.539
were the very siblings who brought it on.

00:40.832 --> 00:41.791
Hold on!

00:41.875 --> 00:43.251
This could get messy!

00:49.215 --> 00:51.176
[energy thrumming]

00:53.595 --> 00:55.388
[both screaming]

00:55.472 --> 00:57.015
[grunting]

00:57.098 --> 00:58.475
[gasping]

00:58.558 --> 00:59.809
-That was...
-Exhilarating.

01:00.769 --> 01:02.062
[groans, wheezing]

01:03.104 --> 01:04.022
Where's Five?

01:04.522 --> 01:05.398
Huh?

01:07.025 --> 01:07.942
Five!

01:08.026 --> 01:10.445
Diego! Allison!

01:11.279 --> 01:12.363
Where is everybody?

01:14.449 --> 01:15.742
Oh, they're gone.

01:16.785 --> 01:20.538
They're gone, like a fart in the wind.
[whimpers]

01:21.039 --> 01:22.040
Poof.

01:22.123 --> 01:25.543
-["Beyond the Sea" playing]
-[Klaus] Just me and you again. Great.

01:26.211 --> 01:28.379
-♪ ...Beyond the sea ♪
-So where the hell are we?

01:28.463 --> 01:31.424
♪ Somewhere, waiting for me ♪

01:33.259 --> 01:35.428
-♪ My lover stands ♪
-[Klaus] Are hats back?

01:35.512 --> 01:38.139
♪ On golden sands... ♪

01:38.223 --> 01:41.184
I think the question is, "When are we?"

01:41.935 --> 01:43.478
Hey! Hey! Excuse me.

01:43.561 --> 01:44.604
Sorry to bother you.

01:44.687 --> 01:46.773
Could you tell me what year this is,

01:46.856 --> 01:48.066
or what day?

01:49.317 --> 01:50.318
Rude.

01:52.070 --> 01:53.822
Klaus! Get over here.

01:53.905 --> 01:57.033
-♪ If I could fly like birds on high... ♪
-[Klaus] Yeah?

01:57.117 --> 01:59.285
-[Ben] Look.
-Yeah, I mean, he's pretty my type,

01:59.369 --> 02:00.286
but I'd have to see him

02:00.370 --> 02:02.372
-from the shoulders down.
-The date, you idiot.

02:02.455 --> 02:03.414
Oh, yeah.

02:03.790 --> 02:06.751
"February 11, 1960"?

02:08.044 --> 02:09.254
1960.

02:11.172 --> 02:12.465
[both] Shit.

02:12.882 --> 02:16.052
[Maxine Nightingale's
"Right Back Where We Started" playing]

02:18.930 --> 02:20.932
[energy crackling]

02:24.769 --> 02:28.439
♪ Ooh, and it's all right
And it's comin' along ♪

02:28.523 --> 02:32.152
♪ We gotta get right back
To where we started from ♪

02:32.235 --> 02:34.946
♪ Love is good, love can be strong ♪

02:35.029 --> 02:38.032
♪ We gotta get right back
To where we started from ♪

02:38.116 --> 02:40.201
[patron chatter ceases]

02:45.498 --> 02:47.000
♪ Do you remember the day ♪

02:47.083 --> 02:48.751
-Oh, shit!
-♪ That sunny day ♪

02:49.169 --> 02:51.671
♪ When you first came my way... ♪

02:53.089 --> 02:54.507
Diego!

02:56.718 --> 02:57.635
Five?

02:59.053 --> 03:00.680
Allison!

03:00.763 --> 03:02.098
[camera shutter clicks]

03:02.182 --> 03:05.101
[both] Allison!

03:06.644 --> 03:10.982
-Allis--
-Allison!

03:11.065 --> 03:12.150
[energy crackling]

03:12.233 --> 03:15.361
-♪ You give me your love ♪
-♪ Give me your love ♪

03:15.445 --> 03:18.698
-♪ I just can't stay away, no, no ♪
-[grunts]

03:18.781 --> 03:22.577
♪ You know you are the oh-oh-only one ♪

03:23.036 --> 03:25.663
-[portal zaps shut]
-♪ Ooh, and it's all right ♪

03:25.747 --> 03:27.123
♪ And it's comin' along... ♪

03:27.207 --> 03:28.791
[woman] Help! Someone help me!

03:31.419 --> 03:33.254
Help! Somebody help me!

03:33.796 --> 03:37.217
♪ We gotta get right back
To where we started from... ♪

03:37.300 --> 03:38.176
[grunts]

03:38.259 --> 03:42.388
[JFK on TV] ...and the glow from that fire
can truly light the world.

03:43.431 --> 03:45.600
And so, my fellow Americans,

03:46.517 --> 03:50.396
ask not what your country can do for you,

03:50.855 --> 03:53.399
ask what you can do for your country.

03:53.483 --> 03:55.944
[audience cheers]

03:56.027 --> 03:57.904
-[energy crackling]
-[grunts]

03:57.987 --> 04:00.573
-[groaning]
-♪ Give me your love ♪

04:00.657 --> 04:03.159
♪ I just can't stay away ♪

04:03.243 --> 04:04.077
[gasping]

04:04.160 --> 04:08.122
♪ You know you are the oh-oh-only one ♪

04:08.206 --> 04:09.332
-[horn honks]
-[tires screech]

04:09.415 --> 04:10.959
-♪ And it's all right ♪
-[grunts]

04:11.042 --> 04:12.835
-♪ And it's comin' along ♪
-[passerby] Oh, no!

04:12.919 --> 04:15.964
♪ We gotta get right back
To where we started from... ♪

04:16.047 --> 04:18.091
[woman] Son of a biscuit.

04:19.259 --> 04:22.804
♪ We gotta get right back
To where we started from ♪

04:22.887 --> 04:25.473
♪ It's all right, and it's comin' along ♪

04:25.556 --> 04:27.976
-♪ We gotta get right back... ♪
-[wind whipping]

04:28.518 --> 04:29.477
[Five] Luther!

04:30.103 --> 04:31.104
Diego!

04:31.604 --> 04:33.815
[distant overlapping gunshots]

04:34.524 --> 04:37.485
-[nearby machine-gun fire]
-[bullets ricocheting]

04:37.568 --> 04:42.073
[man 1 shouts indistinctly]

04:42.156 --> 04:43.574
-[gunshots]
-[man 1 cries out]

04:44.784 --> 04:48.371
-[man 2 speaks rapidly in Russian]
-[overlapping chatter in Russian]

04:51.457 --> 04:53.835
-[indistinct shouts]
-[Five] "Soviets attack US"?

04:54.085 --> 04:56.796
-[machine-gun fire]
-[men shouting in Russian]

04:56.879 --> 04:58.089
[Five] No, this can't be right.

04:58.172 --> 05:00.508
[soldier 1, in English] Gonna get you out.
Keep your head down.

05:00.591 --> 05:02.593
[man shouts in Russian, cries out]

05:02.885 --> 05:05.221
-[soldier 2, in English] Medic! Medic!
-[overlapping shouts]

05:05.722 --> 05:07.056
Hey, kid, get down!

05:07.140 --> 05:09.225
-[man speaks Russian]
-[groans]

05:09.392 --> 05:10.935
[shouts continue]

05:11.853 --> 05:13.813
What the hell did we do now?

05:16.107 --> 05:18.109
[Frank Sinatra's "My Way" playing]

05:23.781 --> 05:25.783
♪ And now ♪

05:26.492 --> 05:28.494
♪ The end is near ♪

05:29.579 --> 05:31.706
♪ And so I face ♪

05:32.707 --> 05:35.001
♪ The final curtain ♪

05:36.419 --> 05:41.090
-♪ My friend, I'll say it clear ♪
-[screaming]

05:41.799 --> 05:44.260
-♪ I'll state my case ♪
-[Luther shouts]

05:45.303 --> 05:48.765
-♪ Of which I'm certain ♪
-[screaming]

05:48.848 --> 05:53.644
♪ I've lived a life that's full ♪

05:53.728 --> 05:54.645
[man yelling]

05:54.729 --> 06:01.194
-♪ I traveled each and every highway ♪
-[overlapping screams]

06:01.277 --> 06:03.571
-♪ And more ♪
-[body splatters]

06:03.738 --> 06:05.740
-Hey!
-♪ Much more than this ♪

06:05.823 --> 06:08.409
I heard a rumor that I blew your minds.
[echoing]

06:08.493 --> 06:12.830
♪ I did it my way ♪

06:17.460 --> 06:19.003
[overlapping shouts]

06:19.087 --> 06:22.298
♪ For what is a man? ♪

06:23.174 --> 06:24.675
♪ What has he got? ♪

06:26.302 --> 06:28.304
♪ If not himself... ♪

06:28.638 --> 06:31.432
Five! You sick son of a bitch,
where the hell have you been?

06:31.516 --> 06:34.185
-[energy zaps]
-♪ To say the things... ♪

06:34.644 --> 06:35.895
If you wanna live, come with me.

06:35.978 --> 06:38.272
Hazel. What the hell's going on here?

06:38.356 --> 06:39.982
There's no time to explain.

06:40.983 --> 06:42.360
Those are nukes, old-timer.

06:43.903 --> 06:46.280
[missiles droning]

06:46.697 --> 06:47.740
What about my family?

06:47.824 --> 06:49.158
You can't save 'em if you're dead.

06:49.242 --> 06:51.369
♪ I took the blows ♪

06:51.953 --> 06:57.417
-♪ And did it my ♪
-[explosions booming]

06:57.500 --> 07:02.213
♪ Way ♪

07:31.993 --> 07:33.077
[energy zaps]

07:38.249 --> 07:39.083
Okay...

07:39.167 --> 07:40.418
what the hell was that?

07:40.501 --> 07:43.504
The end of the world, November 25, 1963.

07:43.880 --> 07:44.964
'63...

07:46.632 --> 07:49.051
[chuckles softly]
You know, Hazel, I'm no history buff,

07:49.135 --> 07:51.137
but I don't recall there being
a nuclear holocaust.

07:51.220 --> 07:52.054
No shit.

07:52.472 --> 07:53.389
What about my family?

07:53.473 --> 07:55.308
Dead, like everyone else.

07:55.975 --> 07:58.311
-And where am I now?
-[Hazel] Dallas. Same street.

07:58.686 --> 07:59.812
Ten days earlier.

08:00.855 --> 08:02.482
Plenty of time to restore the timeline

08:02.565 --> 08:04.025
-and save them.
-[Five whispers] Okay.

08:05.818 --> 08:08.112
-So where do we start?
-"We"? You're on your own, pal.

08:08.196 --> 08:10.364
I'm just here to keep a promise to Agnes.

08:11.157 --> 08:11.991
Is she...?

08:12.575 --> 08:13.534
-Dead?
-Yeah.

08:13.618 --> 08:14.452
Cancer.

08:15.244 --> 08:16.537
[chuckles softly]

08:18.664 --> 08:19.749
Took her quick.

08:20.500 --> 08:23.628
But we had 20 good years together.
I guess forever just wasn't in the cards.

08:26.547 --> 08:28.049
[Five] I'm sorry, Hazel.

08:37.183 --> 08:38.184
What about the Commission?

08:38.267 --> 08:41.604
I quit those assholes, remember?
I don't owe 'em the fuzz off my peaches.

08:45.107 --> 08:47.068
Well then, who the hell are those guys?

08:48.236 --> 08:49.153
[Hazel] Shit.

08:49.612 --> 08:50.571
Run!

08:54.283 --> 08:55.826
[pedestrians screaming]

08:57.078 --> 08:58.704
-[Five gasps]
-[electricity crackling]

09:01.123 --> 09:03.543
[people continue screaming, shouting]

09:09.799 --> 09:10.633
[whistles]

09:10.716 --> 09:13.052
How many times did I say
"bulletproof briefcases"?

09:15.763 --> 09:16.889
[gasps]

09:23.938 --> 09:25.439
-[gunfire stops]
-[racks round]

09:35.950 --> 09:38.286
[Five panting]

09:48.838 --> 09:49.922
[grunts softly]

09:52.925 --> 09:56.429
[old-timey police siren wailing]

09:58.347 --> 10:00.850
[additional police sirens wailing]

10:25.166 --> 10:26.167
What do you want?

10:26.542 --> 10:29.211
Hi, I'm selling encyclopedias
for my youth group.

10:29.295 --> 10:30.254
I was curious if--

10:32.214 --> 10:34.550
[shrieks, panting]

10:34.634 --> 10:35.801
[cutlery clattering]

10:36.636 --> 10:38.304
[panting]

10:39.096 --> 10:39.930
How'd you do that?

10:40.014 --> 10:41.557
Don't really have time to explain.

10:41.641 --> 10:43.726
-You from the Pentagon? Huh?
-Definitely not.

10:43.809 --> 10:46.395
CIA? FBI. KGB?

10:47.021 --> 10:47.897
Is that fresh?

10:49.148 --> 10:51.609
[screams, panting] What...

11:01.494 --> 11:03.621
-Hmm. This Colombian?
-[machine beeps nearby]

11:04.121 --> 11:05.164
It's my own blend.

11:15.257 --> 11:17.718
You ever heard of, uh, Area 51?

11:18.135 --> 11:20.596
-Roswell?
-[man scoffs, chuckles]

11:21.722 --> 11:23.891
[scoffs, chortles]

11:24.308 --> 11:25.935
-Hot damn!
-[knife clatters]

11:26.352 --> 11:28.771
Whoo! See, I always knew
we weren't the only ones.

11:28.854 --> 11:31.148
See, Eleanor thought
my head wasn't screwed on tight,

11:31.232 --> 11:32.483
but... but it's all true, yeah?

11:32.566 --> 11:34.402
UFOs, crop circles...

11:34.485 --> 11:36.028
Well, the truth is out there.

11:36.112 --> 11:38.531
No, no, no, no, no.
The... The truth, it's...

11:39.073 --> 11:40.700
right here in front of us.

11:41.075 --> 11:42.159
Tell me, wh...

11:43.786 --> 11:45.413
why is it always an anal probe?

11:46.622 --> 11:48.541
Any closer, and I'll melt your brain.

11:48.958 --> 11:50.835
He needs a little space. Yes.
I'll be over here.

11:50.918 --> 11:53.671
All those contraptions on the roof,
you built those, right?

11:54.088 --> 11:55.548
Oh, yeah, yeah, sure did.

11:55.756 --> 11:58.467
Yeah, I've been tracking anomalies
in... in the atmosphere.

11:58.968 --> 12:00.845
-Just waiting.
-Waiting for what?

12:01.554 --> 12:02.471
For you.

12:04.306 --> 12:05.224
For all of you.

12:06.183 --> 12:08.728
[man] It all started in 1960,

12:08.811 --> 12:11.147
the year the Silvertone Omega
was released.

12:11.230 --> 12:12.440
I was in the middle of a sale

12:12.523 --> 12:15.109
when something very... strange happened.

12:15.192 --> 12:19.822
This here, the Silvertone Omega,
is one of our top sellers,

12:19.905 --> 12:21.532
in true ColorVision.

12:22.283 --> 12:24.660
Ha! Who knew that Lucy's hair was red?

12:24.744 --> 12:25.578
[chuckles]

12:25.661 --> 12:27.246
[energy crackling outside]

12:30.624 --> 12:33.544
Um, could you just... a moment?

12:37.047 --> 12:40.050
-[Klaus] Diego! Allison!
-[man] So, for the past three years,

12:40.134 --> 12:43.095
I've witnessed five energy surges
in that alleyway out back.

12:43.679 --> 12:45.139
Same thing every time.

12:45.431 --> 12:47.641
A bright blue light,
then something appears.

12:47.725 --> 12:50.186
-Did you get a good look at any of them?
-Yeah, the first one.

12:50.269 --> 12:51.854
And then the big, sensitive one.

12:52.646 --> 12:54.398
-"Sensitive"?
-Yeah, cried a lot,

12:54.482 --> 12:57.902
kept coming back to the alley, sat around
for hours calling a woman's name. Uh...

12:57.985 --> 12:59.528
[snaps fingers] Allison.

12:59.612 --> 13:01.739
-Luther.
-[man] Yeah, he... he wasn't the only one.

13:01.822 --> 13:05.284
Uh, the others came too, off and on
over the years, looking for each other.

13:05.367 --> 13:06.702
Eventually, they... they stopped.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.370
[Five, softly] So, my family is alive.

13:09.288 --> 13:10.122
Shit.

13:10.498 --> 13:13.000
I think I stranded them here.
Now listen to me...

13:13.083 --> 13:15.336
[splutters] Elliott. Elliott.
My name... My name's Elliott.

13:15.419 --> 13:16.879
Whatever, all right?

13:16.962 --> 13:19.548
I got ten days to find them
and save the world.

13:19.840 --> 13:21.550
Now, I need your help to do that.

13:22.301 --> 13:23.803
You need... my...

13:24.261 --> 13:25.346
You know what? I, uh...

13:25.429 --> 13:29.183
I always thought that this, uh, mugshot
looked like arrival number four.

13:30.309 --> 13:31.352
Diego.

13:31.811 --> 13:33.354
-[reading softly]
-[Elliott] So then,

13:34.021 --> 13:36.148
-that's helpful?
-You have no idea.

13:36.232 --> 13:37.983
-[inhaling sharply]
-[energy whooshes]

13:38.400 --> 13:39.276
[exhales heavily]

13:39.360 --> 13:43.322
[woman over PA] Arts and crafts hours
are 1:00 to 3:00 p.m. in the common area.

13:43.405 --> 13:45.574
Pills will be distributed
prior to the start.

13:45.658 --> 13:47.952
[man] Thank you, Alan,
for bringing that to the group.

13:48.035 --> 13:50.454
I think fear is something
we can all relate to.

13:51.497 --> 13:53.415
Okay, who else would like to share?

13:54.291 --> 13:55.209
Anyone?

13:55.543 --> 13:56.669
Come on, who's next?

13:58.712 --> 14:01.507
Diego, you've been awfully quiet
this morning.

14:02.132 --> 14:03.634
Just taking it all in, Doc.

14:03.717 --> 14:05.928
Letting all the healing shit wash over me.

14:06.887 --> 14:08.848
Last week you mentioned your father,

14:09.306 --> 14:12.268
how your whole childhood felt like
some kind of experiment.

14:12.351 --> 14:14.186
-It was an experiment.
-[doctor] Hmm.

14:14.436 --> 14:17.690
-Or did it just feel like an experiment?
-No, it was literally an experiment.

14:20.359 --> 14:23.904
[doctor] Let's dig deeper.
You say your father is a villain.

14:24.029 --> 14:25.781
-Hell, yeah.
-[doctor] So you had to play hero

14:25.865 --> 14:27.366
to make Daddy mad.

14:27.449 --> 14:31.161
[laughing]

14:35.416 --> 14:38.168
-I'm a grown-ass man, Dr. Moncton--
-[Moncton] Who still defines himself

14:38.252 --> 14:39.962
in opposition to his father.

14:40.045 --> 14:41.005
His dead father.

14:41.422 --> 14:43.841
That isn't really defining yourself,
is it, Diego?

14:43.924 --> 14:45.843
Yeah, why don't you tell that
to Luke Skywalker?

14:47.720 --> 14:50.014
I know you don't get it,
but that is an excellent reference.

14:50.097 --> 14:51.140
Humor is good,

14:51.765 --> 14:52.725
truth is better.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.352
Who is the real Diego?

14:57.271 --> 14:58.105
I don't know.

14:59.481 --> 15:00.816
I guess I've never known.

15:05.279 --> 15:06.280
But I'm ready.

15:08.115 --> 15:09.325
I'm ready to find out.

15:21.253 --> 15:22.296
Thank you, Diego.

15:23.547 --> 15:25.758
Okay, quiet time until lunch.

15:27.968 --> 15:28.886
Let me see that.

15:30.387 --> 15:32.473
[whispers, in English accent]
You're so full of shit.

15:32.556 --> 15:34.266
-Tears too much?
-He saw right through it.

15:34.350 --> 15:37.519
-No, he totally ate that shit up.
-Bet you three lunch Jell-Os you're wrong.

15:37.895 --> 15:39.647
-You're on.
-All right.

15:42.775 --> 15:43.859
[Diego] Dr. Moncton.

15:44.693 --> 15:46.445
-Hey, you got a sec?
-Sure, Diego. What is it?

15:46.862 --> 15:49.114
I've been, uh, doing a lot better lately,
haven't I?

15:49.782 --> 15:52.242
True. You're calmer now, less combative.

15:52.326 --> 15:54.244
It's nice to see you opening up in group.

15:56.372 --> 15:58.582
So, uh, when do you think
I might be getting out of here?

15:58.666 --> 16:01.752
Well, your review board
will reassess your case in 90 days.

16:01.835 --> 16:03.921
Ninety days? No, I can't...
I can't wait that long.

16:04.004 --> 16:05.839
Just take it one day at a time. Okay?

16:06.256 --> 16:08.050
No, you don't... you don't understand.

16:08.133 --> 16:10.761
They're going to kill the president
a week from today.

16:10.844 --> 16:13.055
[sighs]
Diego, I thought we moved past this.

16:13.389 --> 16:16.225
-You know what a hero complex is?
-Yeah. It's for assholes

16:16.308 --> 16:18.060
-who think they're heroes--
-This paranoid fantasy

16:18.143 --> 16:19.853
about President Kennedy
is what got you committed

16:19.937 --> 16:21.814
-in the first place.
-They are going to kill him.

16:21.897 --> 16:24.733
They're gonna shoot him in the head
right here in Dallas.

16:24.817 --> 16:26.568
-All right? Understand?
-[Moncton] Let go!

16:26.652 --> 16:27.987
-All right! I'm okay.
-Let go!

16:28.237 --> 16:29.655
I'm sorry. Look, I'm okay.

16:31.198 --> 16:32.658
I'm okay. I'm okay.

16:41.125 --> 16:43.335
[Richard Myhill's "You Must Be an Angel"
plays on radio]

16:44.461 --> 16:45.462
God, this is stupid.

16:45.546 --> 16:47.381
-I can't.
-For you, maybe.

16:48.173 --> 16:49.717
[gasps] This'll cheer you up.

16:52.720 --> 16:53.637
Bacon.

16:53.762 --> 16:56.015
Smuggled it out of the lunchroom.
Do you want some?

16:57.141 --> 16:58.100
No.

16:59.435 --> 17:01.020
[crunches, sighs]

17:03.105 --> 17:05.941
To be honest,
I was saving it for your great escape.

17:09.945 --> 17:11.530
-What are you talking about?
-Just saying,

17:11.613 --> 17:14.408
whatever it is you're planning,
I can be very resourceful.

17:14.491 --> 17:17.327
Look, even if I was planning something,
and I am not,

17:17.411 --> 17:19.538
you would be the last person
I would take.

17:20.664 --> 17:23.083
It's because of the Jell-Os, right?
You can have them back.

17:23.167 --> 17:24.877
No, it's not because of the Jell--

17:26.295 --> 17:29.298
I'm a lone wolf. I don't run with a pack.

17:29.715 --> 17:30.674
Perfect.

17:31.008 --> 17:33.969
Because I'm somewhat
of a lone wolf myself.

17:36.764 --> 17:37.848
[sniffs, groans]

17:38.599 --> 17:41.101
-[sniffs]
-Hargreeves, you have a visitor.

17:41.602 --> 17:43.979
-Who?
-I ain't your secretary.

17:45.189 --> 17:47.524
Maybe Daddy finally came to say,
"I love you."

17:48.317 --> 17:49.651
[mocking English accent] Piss off.

18:00.370 --> 18:02.122
-Five.
-[Five] Hey, Diego.

18:05.209 --> 18:07.377
-[chair scrapes]
-You look good in white.

18:07.878 --> 18:09.338
About time you showed up.

18:09.421 --> 18:12.466
-How'd you know I'd be back?
-Because that's the kind of shit you pull.

18:12.549 --> 18:13.634
Where are the others?

18:14.051 --> 18:15.260
They're not with you?

18:16.261 --> 18:18.097
We'll find them. [mutters softly]

18:18.222 --> 18:20.390
-How long have you been here?
-Seventy-five days.

18:20.474 --> 18:22.476
-[Five grunts softly]
-Landed in the alley behind

18:22.559 --> 18:24.144
-Commerce and Knox.
-Commerce and Knox.

18:24.853 --> 18:26.480
-You?
-I got here this morning.

18:27.439 --> 18:28.607
How'd you find me?

18:28.941 --> 18:30.025
[gentle scoff]

18:31.485 --> 18:32.486
Page 16.

18:33.821 --> 18:37.991
"Disturbed man with multiple knives
arrested outside 1026 N. Beckley."

18:38.283 --> 18:39.993
That's Lee Harvey Oswald's house.

18:40.911 --> 18:41.870
Care to explain?

18:41.954 --> 18:43.163
Let's just say

18:43.247 --> 18:46.250
Dallas Law Enforcement
has not been supportive of my attempt

18:46.333 --> 18:48.502
to stop the assassination of...

18:48.627 --> 18:49.962
[softly] ...John F. Kennedy.

18:50.045 --> 18:52.965
-Because it hasn't happened yet.
-[Diego] And it's not going to happen.

18:53.048 --> 18:54.508
Not on my watch.

18:54.883 --> 18:57.010
Look, I've been shaving down the bars
in my room.

18:57.094 --> 18:59.304
Another day or two,
and I'll be out of this place,

18:59.388 --> 19:02.057
then I'm gonna stop Oswald
and save the president.

19:02.141 --> 19:04.309
You want in, say the word.

19:04.393 --> 19:07.729
[softly] Listen to me very closely,
you gibbering moron.

19:08.272 --> 19:10.190
You are not going to do a goddamn thing.

19:10.274 --> 19:11.650
Why not?

19:11.733 --> 19:14.778
-Because we have to stop the apocalypse.
-[Diego] No shit.

19:14.862 --> 19:16.989
But that doesn't happen
for another 60 years.

19:17.072 --> 19:18.699
Not that apocalypse.

19:18.782 --> 19:20.284
This is a new one.

19:20.951 --> 19:21.994
It followed us.

19:22.536 --> 19:23.537
I've seen it.

19:23.829 --> 19:26.123
Nuclear war, Diego, in ten days.

19:26.206 --> 19:27.624
[laughs softly]

19:31.837 --> 19:33.881
-And I'm the one they locked up, huh?
-[scoffs]

19:33.964 --> 19:35.132
Fine, I'll play along.

19:35.632 --> 19:36.800
What causes it?

19:36.884 --> 19:38.051
I don't know.

19:38.135 --> 19:41.013
Maybe some looney-tuned asshole
with a hero complex

19:41.096 --> 19:43.724
tried to save the president
and screwed everything up.

19:43.807 --> 19:45.726
-So you're saying it worked?
-[scoffs softly]

19:46.101 --> 19:47.477
I saved the president?

19:48.395 --> 19:49.396
[growls softly]

19:49.646 --> 19:50.856
I knew I could do it.

19:52.065 --> 19:54.776
Okay, okay, I'll help you.

19:55.235 --> 19:57.529
-Thank God.
-After I save Kennedy.

19:57.613 --> 19:59.198
And then you swing us back a few decades

19:59.281 --> 20:01.909
so I can slit Hitler's throat off
with a butter knife.

20:02.576 --> 20:04.453
This is why you don't have any friends.

20:06.788 --> 20:07.873
You know what? Guard.

20:07.956 --> 20:10.167
[sighs] My brother is plotting an escape.

20:10.250 --> 20:12.002
The bars of his room
have been shaved down.

20:12.085 --> 20:14.379
-Piece of shit!
-[guard] No! Here-- All right, asshole.

20:14.463 --> 20:16.548
-Look, this is for your own good, Diego.
-No! Five!

20:16.632 --> 20:18.592
-Listen, my brother is a very sick man.
-No, Five!

20:18.926 --> 20:21.386
I only pray that he gets the help
he so desperately needs.

20:22.054 --> 20:24.890
[Diego] No, please! Not the needle! No!
No! No!

20:24.973 --> 20:26.016
[whimpering]

20:26.099 --> 20:28.268
[whispers]
Be back for you later, okay? Just...

20:28.852 --> 20:30.479
Well, nighty night.

20:33.440 --> 20:35.901
-[chickens clucking]
-[cow moos]

20:42.407 --> 20:43.700
[woman] Hey, I'm back.

20:43.784 --> 20:46.286
-[chuckles] Sorry I was gone for so long.
-[door closes]

20:46.370 --> 20:48.872
Did you and Vanya have fun today, Harlan?

20:49.206 --> 20:50.457
[dog barks outside]

20:51.124 --> 20:51.959
We did.

20:52.584 --> 20:55.045
We went down to visit the horses,

20:55.128 --> 20:57.339
and we read James and the Giant Peach.

20:57.422 --> 20:58.632
[rooster crows outside]

20:59.508 --> 21:00.342
Any episodes?

21:00.759 --> 21:01.593
No, ma'am.

21:02.261 --> 21:03.428
[sighs]

21:03.637 --> 21:05.305
How about you? How are you feeling?

21:05.389 --> 21:07.182
Oh, my headaches are a lot better.

21:08.934 --> 21:10.018
Still no memories.

21:10.936 --> 21:14.398
Well then, we just need to get busy
making you some new ones, hmm?

21:18.110 --> 21:19.194
[speakers crackle softly]

21:19.278 --> 21:21.280
[Fran Powers' "Trying" playing]

21:23.573 --> 21:25.450
♪ I'm trying... ♪

21:25.534 --> 21:27.786
[man] I tell ya, Vanya,
I almost got the son of a bitch.

21:27.869 --> 21:30.080
Carl, watch your language around Harlan.

21:30.163 --> 21:31.331
Are you kidding, honey?

21:31.415 --> 21:34.418
If that boy says "son of a bitch,"
I will buy him a BB gun.

21:35.502 --> 21:38.922
Hell, he says any damn thing,
everybody gets a Cadillac. [chuckles]

21:39.548 --> 21:42.092
See, the thing about sales
that people don't get

21:42.175 --> 21:43.719
is the grit.

21:44.261 --> 21:48.181
They think you just show up,
smile real wide, and boom, it's done.

21:48.807 --> 21:50.183
Is that what people think, Carl?

21:50.267 --> 21:51.435
Yes, it is.

21:51.518 --> 21:54.730
But they don't get the art and science
of the thing.

21:54.813 --> 21:57.983
It takes skills to get to that boom.

21:58.066 --> 22:01.528
-Ah! Oh, it's the boom. Mmm.
-Yeah! The boom!

22:01.611 --> 22:04.823
♪ ...In my eyes... ♪

22:04.906 --> 22:06.199
You get any calls yet?

22:07.159 --> 22:09.536
I put another missing persons ad
in the paper.

22:09.619 --> 22:11.455
Figure someone must be searching for ya.

22:11.538 --> 22:14.207
♪ And I love you more and more... ♪

22:14.291 --> 22:16.209
Maybe I'm just not the kind of girl
you miss.

22:16.293 --> 22:18.378
I doubt that very much.

22:18.795 --> 22:20.380
I'm sure we'd miss you already.

22:20.964 --> 22:23.050
-[dishes clinking]
-Well... [clears throat]

22:25.302 --> 22:27.804
-And where do you think you're going?
-[Carl] The office.

22:27.888 --> 22:30.349
I said I almost got 'em.

22:30.849 --> 22:33.810
-I don't got 'em just yet.
-What time will you be home?

22:33.894 --> 22:34.936
[Carl] I don't know.

22:35.020 --> 22:36.772
Depends how hard they make me work

22:36.855 --> 22:39.024
to provide you with this wonderful life.

22:39.107 --> 22:41.068
Fine. Just be quiet when you get back in.

22:41.151 --> 22:43.612
-Don't want you to wake the boy.
-See you in the morning.

22:43.820 --> 22:46.073
[dishes clinking softly]

22:47.699 --> 22:49.326
-Night, Vanya.
-Night, Carl.

22:50.077 --> 22:52.037
-[Carl] Night, Harlan.
-[door closes]

22:52.120 --> 22:54.247
-[faucet running]
-[dishes clinking]

22:56.333 --> 22:59.795
-["Forever and a Day" plays on radio]
-[engine rattles]

23:03.590 --> 23:05.759
[engine sputtering]

23:06.843 --> 23:07.844
[engine stops]

23:07.928 --> 23:09.888
[hissing]

23:10.847 --> 23:11.723
[radio stops]

23:24.194 --> 23:25.570
Now what?

23:25.654 --> 23:28.865
[Ben] Remember when I told you
the engine was overheating?

23:28.949 --> 23:31.618
Yeah, well, being smart
doesn't make you interesting.

23:31.701 --> 23:32.953
Neither does your beard.

23:34.121 --> 23:37.374
You know, it would help if I knew
where we were going, Mysterio.

23:37.457 --> 23:38.417
Back to Dallas.

23:38.500 --> 23:40.585
-That far? For how long?
-[Klaus coughing]

23:41.086 --> 23:43.171
-None of your beeswax.
-Really?

23:43.255 --> 23:46.550
Think I'm just gonna keep following you
everywhere for another three years?

23:46.633 --> 23:48.427
Yeah, you are my ghost bitch.

23:48.510 --> 23:49.428
Remember?

23:50.011 --> 23:53.223
No. We have to go back.
They need you in San Francisco.

23:53.306 --> 23:54.516
They were so clingy.

23:54.599 --> 23:56.226
-Okay, fine!
-Felt like my skin was on fire.

23:56.309 --> 23:58.228
I need us in San Francisco.

23:58.979 --> 24:00.897
I have unfinished business.

24:01.648 --> 24:03.859
Oh. What're you gonna do?

24:03.942 --> 24:07.863
Wear your little ghost power suit
and do some ghost phone calls

24:07.946 --> 24:10.031
-and do some business? Aww!
-Forget it. Forget it.

24:10.115 --> 24:12.659
No, come back.
You have unfinished business.

24:12.742 --> 24:15.245
You don't even have a body without me.

24:15.328 --> 24:16.580
You need me.

24:17.581 --> 24:19.291
Nobody needs your shit, Klaus.

24:19.791 --> 24:21.209
That's why you're always alone.

24:22.335 --> 24:24.754
-Eat shit, you shit-eater!
-[Ben shouts]

24:25.380 --> 24:26.548
Get off!

24:26.965 --> 24:29.009
[both yelling, growling]

24:29.384 --> 24:30.469
[Ben] Ow!

24:30.760 --> 24:31.595
Aah!

24:31.970 --> 24:33.388
Have you showered?

24:33.805 --> 24:35.515
[Ben] Ow! Ow! Ugh! Ow!

24:35.599 --> 24:36.516
[Klaus] No!

24:45.442 --> 24:47.277
[bird of prey screeching]

25:12.594 --> 25:16.097
[Glenn Snow's "I Wonder What
the Future Holds for Me" plays softly]

25:21.269 --> 25:24.147
-[man] You lost, boy? [chuckles]
-[pool balls clatter]

25:24.231 --> 25:26.274
-[Klaus] Thirsty, actually.
-[man] Lord.

25:26.358 --> 25:28.360
[patrons murmuring]

25:29.444 --> 25:31.696
Whoo-hoo. Excusez-moi, garçon.

25:31.780 --> 25:32.697
[bartender] Yeah?

25:32.781 --> 25:36.159
Any idea when the next bus to Dallas
is coming?

25:36.243 --> 25:37.327
Sure do.

25:38.703 --> 25:39.704
And?

25:39.788 --> 25:41.373
[bartender] Three o'clock sharp.

25:42.415 --> 25:43.250
Tomorrow.

25:43.750 --> 25:47.045
Well, that'll mean
plenty more bonding time for-- Okay.

25:48.880 --> 25:50.048
Hey, pretty boy.

25:53.176 --> 25:55.011
-Do you mean me?
-[man] Yeah, you.

25:55.428 --> 25:56.680
You wanna play a little poker

25:56.763 --> 25:57.931
while you wait?

26:01.017 --> 26:03.270
You know what? I would be delighted.

26:10.610 --> 26:13.196
If you keep undressing me with your eyes,

26:13.280 --> 26:14.489
I'm gonna catch cold.

26:14.573 --> 26:15.699
Watch your mouth.

26:16.324 --> 26:17.701
Stupid's falling out.

26:19.953 --> 26:21.454
-[giggles]
-Is something funny?

26:21.538 --> 26:24.624
No, no, just thought of a little ditty
I'm working on.

26:24.708 --> 26:26.960
"There once was a young Buck from Dallas

26:27.502 --> 26:30.755
-who sported a miniature phallus--"
-Tell you what...

26:32.007 --> 26:33.174
if you're so cocky...

26:33.675 --> 26:35.260
what say we up the stakes?

26:35.719 --> 26:37.554
All my money's already in the pot.

26:37.637 --> 26:39.723
Throw in
that sissy-ass gold necklace then.

26:40.181 --> 26:42.475
Clyde here can melt it down,

26:42.559 --> 26:43.977
make me a belt buckle.

26:44.060 --> 26:46.521
That would be one hell of a belt buckle.

26:46.605 --> 26:47.981
He's bluffing, by the way.

26:48.398 --> 26:49.232
He's got nothing.

26:50.525 --> 26:52.152
Okay, I'll put in the sissy necklace

26:52.235 --> 26:53.820
for the keys to your pickup.

26:55.739 --> 26:56.990
Unless you're bluffing.

26:59.451 --> 27:00.285
Deal.

27:02.245 --> 27:03.246
Let's see it.

27:07.626 --> 27:08.960
[chuckles]

27:10.670 --> 27:11.630
Full house.

27:12.088 --> 27:14.174
-Kings over sevens.
-[Klaus chuckles] Oh.

27:14.257 --> 27:15.842
Well, that...

27:17.052 --> 27:18.219
that's not nothing.

27:20.472 --> 27:21.723
Fair is fair. You win.

27:22.182 --> 27:24.643
-And I gotta be on my way.
-You got sticky fingers.

27:24.726 --> 27:27.646
And crazy IBS.
I mean, it's a miracle I'm sitting down--

27:27.729 --> 27:29.773
-[Klaus grunts]
-[glass shattering]

27:30.357 --> 27:32.025
[groans] All right.

27:32.442 --> 27:34.486
-Ow!
-[Buck] Give me my damn keys.

27:37.489 --> 27:38.490
[Klaus] Showtime, Ben.

27:39.991 --> 27:41.493
[Buck] What in the hell?

27:42.243 --> 27:43.370
Nah, I'm good.

27:44.954 --> 27:47.999
You're so independent,
go fight your own battles.

27:48.083 --> 27:50.585
You think you could pick a better time
to self-actualize?

27:50.669 --> 27:52.337
[upbeat guitar music plays]

27:52.420 --> 27:54.756
-[Klaus] I bet you're loving this.
-I'm not hating it.

27:54.839 --> 27:55.924
Shit, which one?

27:56.424 --> 27:58.968
[Buck]
Get your ass back here! You little shit!

28:00.679 --> 28:02.305
-[engine starts]
-[Buck] That's my truck!

28:03.014 --> 28:04.057
Oh, shit.

28:05.308 --> 28:07.060
Give me back my truck, asshole!

28:08.061 --> 28:09.479
[Buck screams]

28:10.188 --> 28:12.774
-You little... [shouts indistinctly]
-[cackling]

28:14.150 --> 28:15.151
[man] Shit!

28:20.323 --> 28:22.992
[dogs barking in distance]

28:24.869 --> 28:26.287
Did you see the paper today?

28:28.623 --> 28:29.624
[keys jingling]

28:30.625 --> 28:31.793
Page one,

28:32.627 --> 28:34.587
paragraph five,

28:35.088 --> 28:36.214
line two:

28:37.048 --> 28:40.844
"When asked about the Southern Justice
Coordinating Committee's upcoming threat

28:40.927 --> 28:42.011
to demonstrate

28:42.095 --> 28:44.556
during President Kennedy's visit
to Dallas,

28:44.848 --> 28:48.560
White House press secretary
Pierre Salinger responded by saying--"

28:48.643 --> 28:51.062
-[woman] What was that?
-We made the papers, baby!

28:51.146 --> 28:53.231
And here's the best part.
You're gonna love this.

28:53.314 --> 28:56.192
And I quote,
"As the president said earlier this year,

28:56.276 --> 28:59.446
-the rights of every man are diminished--"
-"The rights of every man are diminished

28:59.529 --> 29:01.573
when the rights of one man..."

29:02.282 --> 29:04.409
or woman, "...are threatened."

29:04.743 --> 29:05.660
[Allison chuckles]

29:05.744 --> 29:08.580
I bought the last three copies
this morning at Coleman's.

29:10.039 --> 29:11.458
I am the luckiest man in Dallas.

29:11.541 --> 29:13.209
-Is that right?
-That is right.

29:13.293 --> 29:14.127
[laughs]

29:14.210 --> 29:17.297
And you are the most beautiful thing
I have ever seen.

29:17.380 --> 29:18.590
[Allison chuckles]

29:19.174 --> 29:20.675
And the best part of my life.

29:25.180 --> 29:26.139
What?

29:27.974 --> 29:30.185
I just don't want you
to get your hopes up...

29:30.935 --> 29:31.978
about Kennedy.

29:32.937 --> 29:34.814
Change is comin', baby. I can feel it.

29:35.648 --> 29:36.941
-I can feel it.
-[chuckles softly]

29:37.025 --> 29:38.026
Speaking of which...

29:41.571 --> 29:44.032
-[gasps]
-A little pre-anniversary gift

29:44.115 --> 29:45.700
-for my beautiful wife.
-[laughs]

29:45.784 --> 29:48.161
I know I promised you the stars, but...

29:52.415 --> 29:54.751
[chuckles softly] The moon.

29:55.251 --> 29:57.170
I see you staring at it every night.

29:57.504 --> 30:00.465
So now you can see it whenever you want.

30:14.270 --> 30:16.981
[DJ Shadow's "Rocket Fuel
(feat. De La Soul)" playing]

30:17.899 --> 30:19.734
♪ Ladies and gentlemen ♪

30:19.859 --> 30:20.860
♪ Are you ready? ♪

30:22.028 --> 30:23.112
♪ Are you ready? ♪

30:24.197 --> 30:25.448
♪ Get ready ♪

30:27.033 --> 30:28.159
♪ Get ready ♪

30:28.243 --> 30:30.453
-♪ Ready, set ♪
-[men cheering]

30:32.455 --> 30:34.249
♪ Steady, bet ♪

30:35.542 --> 30:37.335
-♪ Get ready ♪
-♪ This be the green light, go ♪

30:37.418 --> 30:38.586
♪ Tires burn the pavement ♪

30:38.670 --> 30:40.797
♪ People wanna know where Mase‚ Pos
And Dave went ♪

30:40.880 --> 30:42.173
♪ Still here, still in your ear ♪

30:42.257 --> 30:44.634
♪ With a style so hot
You'll see where all the sun... ♪

30:44.717 --> 30:46.719
Come on! You can finish him!

30:47.720 --> 30:49.514
♪ The blends be all the right cred ♪

30:49.597 --> 30:51.474
♪ Meaning credentials
Best of both worlds ♪

30:51.558 --> 30:53.643
♪ When we rocking over pearls
In the instrumental ♪

30:53.726 --> 30:55.186
-♪ Are you ready? ♪
-♪ Ready ♪

30:55.270 --> 30:56.145
-♪ Set? ♪
-♪ Set ♪

30:56.229 --> 30:58.022
♪ Jump to the rhythm
As hard as you can go ♪

30:58.106 --> 30:59.274
-♪ Keep it steady ♪
-♪ Steady ♪

30:59.357 --> 31:02.110
♪ To the letter, right?
Turn it up, we giving a show ♪

31:02.193 --> 31:04.404
♪ But can you rock it like rocket fuel? ♪

31:04.946 --> 31:06.072
♪ Space or out your mind ♪

31:06.155 --> 31:07.323
♪ But can you rock it... ♪

31:07.407 --> 31:08.449
-Get him!
-Yeah!

31:08.533 --> 31:10.702
♪ That's a close encounter
Of what kind? ♪

31:12.161 --> 31:13.705
♪ Ready, set ♪

31:15.331 --> 31:16.165
[opponent groans]

31:16.249 --> 31:18.293
-♪ Steady, bet ♪
-Come on!

31:19.377 --> 31:20.628
♪ But can you rock it ♪

31:20.712 --> 31:22.964
-♪ Like rocket fuel? ♪
-[man in crowd shouts indistinctly]

31:25.675 --> 31:27.594
-[crowd chatters excitedly]
-[opponent] Come on!

31:27.677 --> 31:28.845
[grunts, cries out]

31:29.637 --> 31:31.222
-[gasps]
-[knife clatters]

31:31.556 --> 31:33.975
-[opponent screams]
-[crowd] Oh!

31:35.268 --> 31:37.061
[sounds fading]

31:47.655 --> 31:49.782
[crowd chattering, applauding]

31:52.118 --> 31:53.411
Boo!

31:53.494 --> 31:55.580
[man 1] What are you doing?
The hell with you!

31:56.164 --> 31:58.708
-Come on, man.
-[man 2] Tough break!

31:58.791 --> 32:01.794
-[scattered applause]
-[man 3] Next fight! Yeah!

32:01.878 --> 32:03.713
-[man 4] Yeah!
-[man 3] Yeah!

32:06.841 --> 32:07.926
Bring the car around.

32:08.009 --> 32:09.260
[man 3] Next fight!

32:10.303 --> 32:11.471
Attaboy.

32:12.180 --> 32:14.182
-[scattered cheers]
-[men bantering]

32:14.641 --> 32:15.808
[Allison's husband] All right.

32:15.892 --> 32:19.437
All right. Quiet down, now, everyone!
Quiet down. Thank you.

32:20.855 --> 32:22.065
All right, now, look,

32:22.565 --> 32:26.194
I can appreciate that everyone
has concerns about this.

32:26.277 --> 32:29.197
And the truth is,
we can go back and forth on it all night.

32:29.405 --> 32:30.865
But we have to act.

32:31.282 --> 32:33.826
-And the time is now.
-Where are we gonna do it?

32:34.786 --> 32:35.828
[sighs]

32:37.246 --> 32:39.248
-Stadtler's on Commerce.
-[low murmurs]

32:39.332 --> 32:40.583
Okay, look, look, look...

32:40.667 --> 32:42.251
if we start the sit-in on Sunday,

32:42.335 --> 32:44.379
which is five days
before the president's visit,

32:44.462 --> 32:46.923
we should attract
national media attention.

32:47.006 --> 32:49.300
But it has to be
the right kind of attention.

32:49.384 --> 32:50.510
-I agree.
-[group murmurs]

32:50.927 --> 32:55.390
Look, there's no room for error here.
There is no room for images on the TV

32:55.473 --> 32:58.643
of violence, aggression,
or even disrespect.

32:59.018 --> 33:01.896
No matter what they do to us,
we have one rule:

33:02.897 --> 33:05.650
honor and dignity at all times.

33:05.733 --> 33:08.236
Now, look,
these details cannot leave this room

33:08.319 --> 33:09.988
until we have finalized our plan.

33:10.071 --> 33:11.614
-All right?
-[knocking at door]

33:12.657 --> 33:14.242
[knocking continues]

33:16.202 --> 33:17.704
-What should I do?
-Um...

33:17.912 --> 33:19.664
-I'll handle it.
-Allison, wait.

33:21.958 --> 33:22.917
Sorry...

33:23.251 --> 33:25.044
we only cut women's hair here.

33:25.628 --> 33:26.838
Black women's hair.

33:27.213 --> 33:29.507
Funny then that your husband's inside.

33:30.008 --> 33:32.260
Mr. Mason, can I help you?

33:33.803 --> 33:36.848
[Mason] Mind telling me
what you're doing here after hours?

33:36.931 --> 33:39.142
[Allison's husband] Well,
this is my wife's place of employment,

33:39.225 --> 33:41.978
and some nights we use it
as a community gathering spot.

33:42.061 --> 33:44.439
Gathering? For what?

33:44.897 --> 33:46.524
What business is that of yours?

33:46.607 --> 33:49.819
I own the building across the way,
a few others nearby. [sniffs]

33:49.902 --> 33:51.696
I like things quiet on my street.

33:52.780 --> 33:55.033
But you don't own this building,
now, do you?

33:55.658 --> 33:56.701
[clicks tongue]

33:56.951 --> 33:57.827
Not yet.

33:57.910 --> 33:58.786
[chuckles softly]

33:58.870 --> 34:01.122
Well then, I'm gonna ask you
to step off the property.

34:01.622 --> 34:02.498
Have a good night.

34:07.211 --> 34:10.840
Did you just deliberately
shut this door on my foot, boy?

34:11.466 --> 34:12.800
That's assault.

34:14.302 --> 34:15.344
[gasps, grunts]

34:15.428 --> 34:16.971
[people gasp, murmur]

34:20.308 --> 34:22.310
-[man 1] She ain't playin' around.
-[man 2 chuckles]

34:22.393 --> 34:24.228
[man 1] Don't mess with her. Damn.

34:27.023 --> 34:28.441
I hope that felt good.

34:28.816 --> 34:29.984
You have no idea.

34:37.617 --> 34:39.535
So much for honor and dignity.

34:39.952 --> 34:40.953
Him first.

34:43.456 --> 34:45.458
Y'all can go on about your business now.

34:48.753 --> 34:50.755
[insects chirring]

34:56.886 --> 34:59.639
[Vanya] I can't sleep.
Is there any of that cake left?

35:02.683 --> 35:03.643
Sissy...

35:04.519 --> 35:05.853
are you smoking?

35:08.856 --> 35:10.233
[chuckles]

35:10.316 --> 35:11.234
[laughs]

35:12.527 --> 35:14.654
-Want one?
-["Be Thankful You're You" plays softly]

35:15.238 --> 35:18.366
[Sissy] Mama would die all over again
if she saw me right now.

35:20.284 --> 35:22.745
[Vanya] Never would've guessed
you had such a rebellious side.

35:22.829 --> 35:25.039
[Sissy chuckles] Men have sides.

35:25.748 --> 35:26.999
Women have secrets.

35:28.709 --> 35:30.086
And what are your secrets?

35:31.712 --> 35:33.214
I have an escape plan.

35:34.298 --> 35:35.174
What? [chuckles]

35:35.258 --> 35:36.884
There is a coffee can

35:37.635 --> 35:39.846
hidden under the kitchen sink.

35:40.513 --> 35:42.890
Every penny I save
that Carl doesn't know about

35:42.974 --> 35:44.976
-goes in there.
-Why?

35:45.893 --> 35:47.728
[sighs] So I can breathe.

35:48.813 --> 35:51.149
Carl's a fine man, a good man, but...

35:52.400 --> 35:54.402
good men still leave.

35:55.444 --> 35:56.404
Or die.

35:58.489 --> 36:00.783
Sooner or later,
every woman has to fend for herself.

36:02.326 --> 36:03.369
How'd you two meet?

36:03.452 --> 36:04.787
Because of a lie.

36:06.747 --> 36:07.999
My sister told me

36:08.082 --> 36:10.585
she wanted to go see a boy,
but really she was bringing me.

36:11.460 --> 36:13.087
I was too shy for my own good back then.

36:13.796 --> 36:15.006
Carl means well,

36:15.464 --> 36:18.009
works hard, loves his boy.

36:18.551 --> 36:20.803
But I had silly dreams back then.

36:21.721 --> 36:23.097
What did you want to be?

36:24.265 --> 36:26.392
A counter girl at Neiman Marcus.

36:27.268 --> 36:28.978
[chuckles softly] Really?

36:29.061 --> 36:30.855
Daddy took us there once a year

36:30.938 --> 36:32.440
to buy perfume for Christmas.

36:33.900 --> 36:35.401
It was magical.

36:36.986 --> 36:40.907
Music, dresses, the smells.

36:41.824 --> 36:45.369
All the ladies at the counters
looked like livin' dolls. Still do.

36:46.162 --> 36:49.373
Could you ever imagine bein' that elegant?

36:52.501 --> 36:53.544
Hey.

36:55.630 --> 36:56.964
You're plenty elegant.

37:04.680 --> 37:07.266
[Daniela Andrade's "Crazy" playing]

37:25.117 --> 37:26.661
♪ I remember when ♪

37:26.744 --> 37:30.164
♪ I remember
I remember when I lost my mind ♪

37:31.791 --> 37:34.001
♪ There was something so pleasant
About that place ♪

37:34.085 --> 37:35.419
[grunting]

37:35.503 --> 37:37.630
-♪ Even your emotions have an echo ♪
-[joint dislocates]

37:37.713 --> 37:39.715
-[groans]
-♪ In so much space ♪

37:39.799 --> 37:41.050
[gasping]

37:44.637 --> 37:46.138
♪ And when you're out there ♪

37:46.222 --> 37:47.265
♪ Without care ♪

37:47.348 --> 37:49.934
♪ Yeah, I was out of touch ♪

37:50.017 --> 37:51.102
[groaning]

37:51.185 --> 37:54.397
♪ But it wasn't because
I didn't know enough ♪

37:57.316 --> 37:59.735
♪ I just knew too much ♪

38:02.238 --> 38:06.492
♪ Does that make me crazy? ♪

38:07.076 --> 38:11.580
♪ Does that make me crazy? ♪

38:11.664 --> 38:12.581
[lock rattling]

38:12.665 --> 38:16.419
♪ Does that make me crazy? ♪

38:17.128 --> 38:20.923
♪ Possibly ♪

38:21.382 --> 38:23.009
[grunts softly]

38:24.260 --> 38:26.220
♪ Pa-pa-pe ♪

38:26.637 --> 38:28.639
♪ Pa-pa-pa-pe ♪

38:29.015 --> 38:31.100
♪ Pa-pa-pa-pe ♪

38:31.392 --> 38:32.393
♪ Pa-pa-pa-pe ♪

38:36.022 --> 38:37.106
[engine stops]

38:38.899 --> 38:41.027
[bottles clinking]

38:42.111 --> 38:44.572
-[hinges creaking]
-[bottles rattling softly]

38:54.290 --> 38:55.791
Little late for milk, don't you think?

38:59.670 --> 39:01.672
[suspenseful instrumental music plays]

39:04.342 --> 39:05.593
[empty shell clatters]

39:23.319 --> 39:24.653
[grunts softly]

39:28.324 --> 39:29.742
[panting]

39:29.992 --> 39:31.702
[groans softly]

39:33.496 --> 39:34.955
-Ah, shit.
-Hargreeves.

39:35.331 --> 39:37.541
-What are you doing out here?
-I'm sleepwalking.

39:38.501 --> 39:40.086
[grunts, cries out]

39:40.795 --> 39:42.588
Like to run your mouth, smart-ass?

39:42.671 --> 39:44.673
It's gonna be hard after I break your jaw.

39:44.757 --> 39:45.966
-[metal clangs]
-[body thuds]

39:46.050 --> 39:47.259
[giggles]

39:47.343 --> 39:48.177
[Diego] Lila?

39:48.260 --> 39:50.429
You're not the only one
who wants out, wolf man!

39:50.513 --> 39:51.889
[Diego groans, cries out]

39:51.972 --> 39:53.766
Watch my shoulder. [grunts]

39:53.849 --> 39:56.018
[Mel Tormé's "Comin' Home Baby" playing]

39:56.102 --> 39:57.812
-[whispers] How'd you get out?
-♪ Do-do-do ♪

39:57.895 --> 40:00.648
-♪ I'm comin' home, baby, now ♪
-♪ Do-do-do-do-do-do-do-do ♪

40:00.731 --> 40:03.442
♪ I'm comin' home now right away... ♪

40:03.526 --> 40:05.069
-[joint pops in]
-[both scream]

40:05.152 --> 40:06.112
[howling]

40:06.195 --> 40:09.782
-[continues howling]
-♪ I'm sorry now I ever went away ♪

40:09.865 --> 40:14.495
-♪ Do-do-do-do-do ♪
-♪ Every night and day I go and stay ♪

40:15.830 --> 40:18.040
-♪ I'm comin' home, baby ♪
-♪ Come on home ♪

40:18.124 --> 40:20.835
-♪ Comin' home, baby, now ♪
-♪ You know I'm waitin' here for you ♪

40:20.918 --> 40:23.504
♪ I'm comin' home now, real soon ♪

40:23.587 --> 40:24.672
♪ You been gone ♪

40:24.755 --> 40:25.965
♪ Comin' home, baby, now ♪

40:26.048 --> 40:27.800
♪ You don't know what I'm gonna do ♪

40:27.883 --> 40:29.969
♪ I'm comin' home
I know I'm over you ♪

40:30.052 --> 40:32.054
♪ Since you went away... ♪

40:33.180 --> 40:34.056
[Lila screams]

40:40.938 --> 40:43.190
♪ They can't hold me back now
No more ♪

40:43.274 --> 40:44.608
-[Diego] Go, go!
-♪ Come along ♪

40:44.692 --> 40:46.318
-[Lila] Who are those guys?
-[Diego] No idea.

40:46.402 --> 40:48.112
♪ Chase me up and down the floor... ♪

40:48.696 --> 40:51.407
-What the hell are you stopping for?
-We need a distraction.

40:51.699 --> 40:53.325
-Follow me.
-[patients screaming]

40:53.993 --> 40:55.119
[bullets ricocheting]

40:56.036 --> 40:57.079
♪ I'm comin' home ♪

40:57.163 --> 40:58.831
-♪ Come on home ♪
-[people screaming]

40:58.914 --> 41:01.667
-♪ You're hearing what I say ♪
-♪ That you're comin' home ♪

41:01.750 --> 41:05.171
♪ And I never will go away ♪

41:06.338 --> 41:07.548
♪ I'm comin' home... ♪

41:32.740 --> 41:34.366
-Which way?
-Right.

41:34.450 --> 41:36.118
-Why right?
-Why not?

41:36.452 --> 41:37.453
[whispers] Okay.

41:40.998 --> 41:42.875
-[Diego grunts]
-[Lila panting]

41:42.958 --> 41:44.710
-[Diego groans]
-Thank God you're here.

41:44.793 --> 41:46.420
Three men just tried to attack us.

41:46.504 --> 41:48.172
-Get your hands up, now.
-[Lila gasping]

41:48.255 --> 41:50.257
Wait, you don't understand.
We're not the bad guys.

41:50.341 --> 41:52.009
Shut your mouth and stay on the ground.

41:52.092 --> 41:54.303
-[grunts, groans]
-[Lila grunts]

41:55.095 --> 41:56.972
[panting]

41:57.056 --> 41:58.724
Where'd you learn how to fight like that?

41:59.225 --> 42:00.142
My mother.

42:00.309 --> 42:01.769
-Come on.
-♪ Comin' home ♪

42:01.852 --> 42:03.187
♪ I'm comin' home, baby, now ♪

42:03.270 --> 42:04.772
♪ You know I'm waitin' at the door ♪

42:04.855 --> 42:07.691
♪ They can't hold me back now
No more ♪

42:07.775 --> 42:09.193
-♪ Come along ♪
-[guard] Don't shoot.

42:09.276 --> 42:10.861
-♪ I'm comin' home, baby, now ♪
-[groans]

42:10.945 --> 42:12.112
♪ Come on home ♪

42:12.196 --> 42:15.783
-♪ I'm comin' home, baby, now ♪
-[alarm blaring]

42:17.660 --> 42:19.995
-[alarm continues blaring]
-[patients chattering excitedly]

42:25.292 --> 42:27.294
[excited shouts]

42:30.464 --> 42:33.592
[Jim Boyd's "You Only Want Me
When You're Lonely" playing]

42:35.678 --> 42:37.513
[men whistling, cheering]

42:38.180 --> 42:40.015
♪ You only want me ♪

42:40.099 --> 42:41.809
♪ Oh, when you're lonely ♪

42:41.892 --> 42:44.895
-♪ You only want me then ♪
-[overlapping chatter]

42:45.396 --> 42:47.106
-♪ You only need me ♪
-[man whistling]

42:47.189 --> 42:48.816
♪ When you're lonesome ♪

42:48.899 --> 42:50.901
♪ It's then and only then ♪

42:52.528 --> 42:54.113
♪ You only want me... ♪

42:54.697 --> 42:55.823
Hi, Luther.

42:56.407 --> 42:58.450
Hey, Autumn. How's business?

42:58.534 --> 43:00.786
Still waiting for the big tippers
to show up.

43:02.079 --> 43:04.164
[Luther]
Who's the half-wit bothering Mr. Ruby?

43:04.248 --> 43:05.082
[Autumn] No idea,

43:05.165 --> 43:08.419
but he's been putting away vodka gimlets
like they're gonna run out of limes.

43:08.836 --> 43:10.504
Oh, yeah? He give you any trouble?

43:10.588 --> 43:11.505
Not yet.

43:11.589 --> 43:12.840
We should do business, Jack.

43:13.215 --> 43:15.342
-[Autumn] But he's getting there.
-[Carl] I can get you a deal

43:15.426 --> 43:17.219
-on good showerheads.
-You guys want some more?

43:17.303 --> 43:18.262
We okay here?

43:20.014 --> 43:21.473
I'm more worried about the kid.

43:22.141 --> 43:23.017
What kid?

43:23.350 --> 43:24.310
By the stage.

43:24.935 --> 43:26.937
I told him we don't allow minors.

43:27.980 --> 43:28.981
Oh, yeah?

43:29.815 --> 43:30.858
And what'd he say?

43:30.941 --> 43:33.861
[chuckles]
He asked what time I was getting off work.

43:34.737 --> 43:36.113
[Autumn laughs softly]

43:40.868 --> 43:42.369
She's too young for you.

43:43.370 --> 43:44.830
Nice to see you too, Luther.

43:44.913 --> 43:46.123
What do you want?

43:46.582 --> 43:48.667
For you to stop hovering
like an ambitious stripper

43:48.751 --> 43:49.752
and sit down with me.

43:54.882 --> 43:56.008
How long have you been here?

43:57.259 --> 43:58.927
A year, thanks to you.

43:59.011 --> 44:01.180
I'm sorry, Luther.
I know that couldn't have been easy.

44:01.263 --> 44:02.598
I thought everybody was dead.

44:02.681 --> 44:04.558
[Carl] Come on, Jack! Don't make me beg!

44:04.850 --> 44:06.727
-[Jack] Just back off.
-I gotta go.

44:07.061 --> 44:07.978
Luther, wait.

44:08.771 --> 44:10.064
Look, I get it, okay?

44:10.439 --> 44:12.775
I know what it's like
to be stuck in time...

44:12.858 --> 44:13.776
[siren wailing]

44:13.859 --> 44:16.695
...thinking this is how you're gonna
live out the rest of your life.

44:18.155 --> 44:19.114
On the run,

44:19.490 --> 44:22.743
and not knowing if you're ever gonna see
the people you love again,

44:22.826 --> 44:24.995
and to be in an unfamiliar world.

44:25.079 --> 44:27.081
But Luther, you're not alone.

44:27.247 --> 44:28.540
We have to find the others

44:28.624 --> 44:31.585
because the world ends again in ten days.

44:32.294 --> 44:34.088
I have no idea how to stop it.

44:39.760 --> 44:40.886
I don't give a shit.

44:46.350 --> 44:49.269
[rock violin music playing]
